13 April - Pizza Dolce Di Ricotta

One batch Pasta Frolla

Filling: 
- 1 1/2 lb ricotta cheese
- 1/2   cup sugar
- 4     eggs
- 1     teaspoon vanilla
- 1     tablespoon anisette
- 3     tablespoon chopped candied citron or orange peel
- 1     teaspoon ground cinnamon

Egg wash:
- 1 egg, beaten with dash of salt

Prepare Pasta Frolla. Wrap and chill until needed. 
To prepare Ricotta filling, place ricotta cheese in mixing bowl and stir in sugar. Stir in eggs, one at a time to make smooth creamy mixture. Stir in vanilla, anisette, citron, and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Butter 9" cake pan, 2" deep. To Assemble, cut off 1/3 of Pasta Frolla and set aside. Roll remaining 2/3 of dough into 14" disco and ease into prepare pan. Allow dough to hang over edge of pan. Spoon in ricotta filling and psread evently. Sprinkle filling with remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. 
Roll remiaing 1/3 of dough into 10" square. Cut into 10 1" wide strips. Paint strips with egg wash. Moisten rim of dough on pan with egg wash and adhere 5 strips in each direction, forming diagonal lattic.e Trim excess dough even with top of pan and push dough off top rim so it is completely within pan. 

Bake on bottom rack (set at lowest level) at 350F for about 45 minutes, until filling is set and pastry is light golden. Cool in pan before unmolding. To unmold, invert onto flat plate. Lift off pan. Replace pan with another plate or platter and reinvert so pizza is right side up. Serve at room temperature. Makes about 10 servings. 